{"CUP":[{"def":"Repeated potations; social or exessive indulgence in intoxicating drinks; revelry.","pos":""},{"def":"A cupping glass or other vessel or instrument used to produce the vacuum in cupping.","pos":""}],"CUP SHAKE":[{"def":"A shake or fissure between the annual rings of a tree, found oftenest near the roots.","pos":""}],"CUP-GALL":[{"def":"A kind of oak-leaf gall.","pos":""}],"CUP-MOSS":[{"def":"A kind of lichen, of the genus Cladonia.","pos":""}],"CUPBEARER":[{"def":"One of the attendants of a prince or noble, permanently charged with the performance of this office for his master.","pos":""}],"CUPBOARD":[{"def":"A board or shelf for cups and dishes.","pos":""},{"def":"A small closet in a room, with shelves to receive cups, dishes, food, etc.","pos":""}],"CUPEL":[{"def":"A shallow porus cup, used in refining precious metals, commonly made of bone ashes (phosphate of lime).","pos":""}],"CUPELLATION":[{"def":"The act or process of refining gold or silver, etc.","pos":""}],"CUPFUL":[{"def":"As much as a cup will hold.","pos":""}],"CUPID":[{"def":"The god of love, son of Venus; usually represented as a naked, winged boy with bow and arrow.","pos":""}],"CUPIDITY":[{"def":"A passionate desire; love.","pos":""},{"def":"Eager or inordinate desire, especially for wealth; greed of gain; avarice; covetousness.","pos":""}],"CUPOLA":[{"def":"A roof having a rounded form, hemispherical or nearly so; also, a celing having the same form.","pos":""},{"def":"The top of the spire of the cochlea of the ear.","pos":""}],"CUPPER":[{"def":"One who performs the operation of cupping.","pos":""}],"CUPPING":[{"def":"The operation of drawing blood to or from the surface of the person by forming a partial vacuum over the spot.","pos":""}],"CUPPY":[{"def":"Hollow; cuplike; also, full of cups, or small depressions.","pos":""},{"def":"Characterized by cup shakes; -- said of timber.","pos":""}],"CUPREOUS":[{"def":"Consisting of copper or resembling copper; coppery.","pos":""}],"CUPRIC":[{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or derived from, copper; containing copper; -- said of those compounds of copper in which this element is present in its lowest proportion.","pos":""}],"CUPRIFEROUS":[{"def":"Containing copper; as, cupriferous silver.","pos":""}],"CUPRITE":[{"def":"The red oxide of copper; red copper; an important ore of copper, occurring massive and in isometric crystals.","pos":""}],"CUPROID":[{"def":"Cu\"proid (k\"proid), n.","pos":""}],"CUPROUS":[{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or derived from, copper; containing copper; -- said of those compounds of copper in which this element is present in its highest proportion.","pos":""}],"CUPULATE":[{"def":"Having or bearing cupeles; cupuliferous.","pos":""}],"CUPULE":[{"def":"A cuplet or little cup, as the acorn; the husk or bur of the filbert, chestnut, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"A sucker or acetabulum.","pos":""}],"CUPULIFEROUS":[{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or resembling, the family of plants ot which the oak and the chestnut are examples, -- trees bearing a smooth, solid nut inclosed in some kind of cup or bur; bearing, or furnished with, a cupule.","pos":""}]}